title: Plant Propagation
description: An illustration showing the process of plant propagation. On the left, a healthy plant with green leaves is being pruned with a pair of red-handled pruning shears. An arrow points from the pruned plant to the right, where a small plant with roots is depicted in a pot, indicating the process of taking a cutting and planting it.

title: Grafted Tree Branch
description: An illustration of a tree branch that has been grafted. The branch shows a fresh green shoot emerging from a cut area, which is wrapped with a white bandage. There are additional small green leaves sprouting nearby, indicating new growth.

title: Harvested Potatoes
description: The image shows freshly harvested potatoes in soil. Some potatoes are partially buried, while others are visible on the surface, surrounded by dirt and roots from the plant.

title: Ginger Roots
description: An image showing freshly harvested ginger roots partially covered in soil. The roots are knobby and irregular in shape, with some green shoots visible above the ground.

title: Strawberry Plants
description: A close-up view of strawberry plants featuring ripe red strawberries and unripe green ones, surrounded by green leaves and soil.
